        "types-copy": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "Section copy",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Golden uses mānuka and kānuka honey. They are both native New Zealand honeys, but they do not taste the same. Mānuka tends to be darker, richer, and more resinous. Kānuka is usually lighter and more floral. We choose between them for flavour balance, not because one sounds more fashionable than the other. If you want the side-by-side explanation, read our <a href=\"/pages/manuka-vs-kanuka\" title=\"Mānuka vs Kānuka\">mānuka vs kānuka guide</a>.</p>",
